            <h2>Your interim Paddlesports North America (PNA) Board invites you to vote for the first formally elected PNA Board Members.<br /><small>Voting is open through October 13th.</small></h2>

            <p>Before you vote, there are a few things you need to know:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Your PNA membership must be current and you need to know your PNA membership number to vote. If you cannot locate your membership number, please send an email to <a href="mailto:info@paddlesportsnorthamerica.org" target="_blank">info@paddlesportsnorthamerica.org</a> and request it. Please check now. It will likely be challenging to accommodate last minute requests.</li>
              <li>You must be resident in North America at the time of voting.</li>
              <li>The PNA by-laws allows one vote per membership. This means that if you have a PNA Family Membership, there is one vote per family. Please delegate a single family member to vote as multiple votes are void.</li>
              <li>It is highly recommended that you review the <a href="http://www.paddlesportsnorthamerica.org/about/candidates">brief bios of the candidates</a> before voting.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>You can then vote in one of two ways:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>IN PERSON VOTING:</strong> If you are attending the PNA Annual Meeting, you can vote in person by completing the required proxy statement and ballot available at the meeting. Please arrive at least 15 minutes early to assure you have ample time to complete the ballot and have your vote counted. Once the meeting commences, voting is officially over.</li>
              <li><strong>ELECTRONIC VOTING:</strong> If you are not attending the meeting, you can <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/VFWTD5V" target="_blank">vote electronically by completing the proxy statement and ballot using the PNA online voting system</a>. Electronic voting will be closed at October 13 at 5 p.m. Eastern Time.
            </ul>
            <p>If you are voting electronically, you can do so right now as voting is open, so grab your PNA membership number and <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/VFWTD5V" target="_blank">vote for your PNA Board now</a>.
          </div>
        
          <div>
            <h2>Announcement from the Board - The first annual PNA meeting is October 16, 2015.</h2>
            <p><strong>Mark your calendars for Friday, October 16, 2015 at 9 a.m.</strong> for the first annual meeting of Paddlesports North America (PNA). This milestone event will be held in Pacific City, Oregon after BCU week and before the Lumpy Waters Sea Kayak Symposium.  At this meeting, we will discuss our accomplishments, challenges and plans for the next few years and elect the first official PNA Board and Executive team.</p>

            <p>Can’t make it? Don’t worry. You will still be able to vote for your board through the wizardry of modern technology in advance of the meeting. Election results and meeting minutes will be posted on the PNA website shortly after the meeting. (We do want to go paddling; after all, we’re in Oregon!)</p>

            <p>Want to be a member of the Executive team (President, Vice President, Secretary or Treasurer) or want to be a board member-at-large? Please nominate yourself by emailing your name, position of interest and a paragraph about why you would make a good board member to Harry Tobin, Interim Board President at <a href="mailto:Htobin001@gmail.com" target="_blank">Htobin001@gmail.com</a>. The deadline for submissions is September 4 at 5 p.m. Eastern Time. To see examples of nomination paragraphs, check out the current blurbs of the interim board members at <a href="http://www.paddlesportsnorthamerica.org/about#board">http://www.paddlesportsnorthamerica.org/about#board</a>.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <h2>Paddlesports North America Coach Educator Opportunities!</h2>
            <p>Paddlesports North America, in conjunction with British Canoeing has identified a need for Level 1 and 2 Coach Educators in North America. With that in mind, PNA is opening applications for no more than 6, Level 1 and 2 Coach Educators. Applications for Tutor and Assessor roles will be considered from active and updated coaches with a minimum of a Level 3 Qualification or Moderate Water Endorsement.</p>
            <p>The strongest applications will be selected considering the following:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Depth and bredth of coaching qualifications / experience</li>
              <li>Tutoring or teaching qualification/experience</li>
              <li>Assessing qualifications/experience</li>
              <li>Knowledge and understanding of the award syllabus</li>
              <li>Fit to Paddlesports North America workforce demands</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Application packs are available on request from <a href="mailto:fiona.fuller@britishcanoeing.org.uk" target="_blank">fiona.fuller@britishcanoeing.org.uk</a>. The closing date for submission of applications is July 24, 2015.</p>
            <p>Successful applicants will be invited to progress to an orientation on October 6-7, 2015 in Boothbay, ME, after which they will be required to work through an individualized action plan supporting delivery on courses and completing a portfolio of evidence tracking their development.</p>
            <p>For complete information on the Level 1 and 2 Coach Educator descriptions and requirements refer to: <a href="http://paddlesportsnorthamerica.s3.amazonaws.com/downloads/bcuab-coach-educator-requirements-v2-2x.pdf" target="_blank">BCUAB Coach Educator Requirements</a>. The need for Coach Educators will be reviewed periodically and a call for future applicants made in 2016 if identified as needed.</p>
          </div>
          
